CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1944, pg. 13, reads: "BILLY ECKSTINE, the fames orchestra leader, seems intrigued at whatever that is Lena is showing him at the reception given in her honor at the nationally known Loendi Club last Wednesday night. - Staff Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Billy Eckstine, and Lena Horne wearing striped suit, holding item and standing behind cake, with Miriam Sharpe Fountain in background, in Loendi Club, for reception in honor of Lena Horne, another version
